.:: Puzzle 4x5-Level-2-19::.
5 different games are played: snooker, canasta, billiard, whist, monopoly
There 5 different types of food: lime, cauliflower, mango, cherry, pomegranate
House: gothic-revival, colonial, farmhouse, craftsman, art-deco
The people prefer 5 different types of sport: rowing, ice-hockey, cricket, volleyball, cycling
 1. the art-deco house is on the right of the person who's sport is ice-hockey##1
 2. the person eating cherry is on the left of the person eating cauliflower##1
 3. the person playing monopoly is on the left of the person who's sport is cycling##1
 4. the person who's sport is cricket is on the far left##1
 5. the colonial house is between the person eating lime and the gothic-revival house##2
 6. the person eating lime is on the far left##1
 7. the person playing billiard is between the person who's sport is rowing and the person playing monopoly##2
 8. the person playing canasta is between the person playing whist and the person playing snooker##2
 9. the craftsman house is on the left of the person playing snooker##1
10. the person playing snooker is on the right of the person eating pomegranate##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |      2      |     3     |     4      |     5      |
| Game         | monopoly  | billiard | whist   | canasta      | snooker |
| Food   | lime   | cherry    | cauliflower | pomegranate | mango      |
| House           | farmhouse | colonial    | gothic-revival       | craftsman     | art-deco      |
| Sport     | cricket | cycling        | rowing  | ice-hockey        | volleyball    |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 4x5-Level-2-20::.
The people have 5 different jobs:  accountant, paramedic, analyst, architect, police-officer
5 different games are played: snooker, monopoly, poker, backgammon, mah-jongg
The people's birthday is in 5 different months: november, september, april, january, may
There 5 different types of food: cauliflower, asparagus, strawberry, garlic, tomato
 1. the accountant is on the left of the person playing snooker##1
 2. the person playing mah-jongg is between the person eating garlic and the person who's birthday is in may##2
 3. the person who's birthday is in may is on the right of the police-officer##1
 4. the person playing mah-jongg is the person who's birthday is in november##1
 5. the person who's birthday is in november is between the person eating tomato and the person who's birthday is in april##2
 6. the person eating tomato is on the right of the police-officer##1
 7. the person playing poker is the person who's birthday is in january##1
 8. the architect is the person who's birthday is in september##1
 9. the person eating cauliflower is the person who's birthday is in september##1
10. the architect is on the right of the person eating strawberry##1
11. the person playing mah-jongg is on the left of the paramedic##1
12. the person playing monopoly is on the far left##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |     2      |    3    |      4       |       5       |
| Job         | analyst    | police-officer  | paramedic  | accountant      | architect |
| Game   | monopoly    | mah-jongg   | backgammon | poker | snooker   |
| Birthday   | april | november    | may    | january       | september         |
| Food   | garlic  | asparagus | tomato    | strawberry     | cauliflower      |

 